      Executive comp
   =20
 =20
What happened  here?Jamie Dimon=E2=80=99s five-year retirement joke just go=
t serious.The billionaire chief executive officer of JPMorgan Chase & Co. w=
as granted a special gift to persuade him to lead the biggest U.S. lender f=
or another =E2=80=9Csignificant number of years.=E2=80=9D He was awarded 1.=
5 million stock appreciation rights, which are like options and will let hi=
m capture a profit if the stock price rises in the coming years. =E2=80=A6=
=E2=80=9CThis special award reflects the board=E2=80=99s desire for Mr. Dim=
on to continue to lead the firm for a further significant number of years,=
=E2=80=9D JPMorgan=E2=80=99s board said in a regulatory filing Tuesday.Dimo=
n=E2=80=99s options are worth around $50 million on paper, according to Ter=
ry Adamson, an equity-valuation specialist who=E2=80=99s the managing direc=
tor of Technical Compensation Advisors. JPMorgan didn=E2=80=99t disclose it=
s own valuation of them.The board gave the award to motivate Dimon, who alr=
eady has a $2.1 billion fortune, to keep doing his job well. Dimon, who rec=
eived $31.5 million in compensation for 2020, won=E2=80=99t be able to exer=
cise the options for at least five years, and must hold any net shares gain=
ed from the award until mid-2031.July is not a particularly traditional tim=
e for financial-industry bonuses? Was he =E2=80=A6=C2=A0considering taking =
another job? Did he get an exciting=C2=A0offer to build a mid-tier regional=
 bank into a global powerhouse, and JPMorgan scrambled to match it? Or did =
he come to the board and say =E2=80=9Chey I=E2=80=99ve been doing this for =
a long time, I=E2=80=99ve had a good run, I=E2=80=99ve accomplished most of=
 what I want to accomplish, I=E2=80=99ve provided well for my family what w=
ith my $2.1 billion fortune, and now I=E2=80=99d like to retire and spend m=
ore time with them=E2=80=9D and the board was like =E2=80=9Coh no, we need =
you to stick around for another decade, would increasing your net worth by =
2.4% change your mind=E2=80=9D and he was like =E2=80=9Coh man I could real=
ly use 50 million more dollars, I=E2=80=99ll do it=E2=80=9D?=C2=A0My model =
for executive compensation at the very high end =E2=80=94=C2=A0where Dimon =
and, like, Elon Musk reside =E2=80=94=C2=A0is that these are people who hav=
e moved beyond being motivated by money, who cannot realistically buy any m=
ore lifestyle with more money, but it=E2=80=99s still nice to feel loved, a=
nd the love language of a public-company board is pretty much always going =
to be options grants. My model is that the board got together and said =E2=
=80=9Chey Jamie has been doing a great job lately but he looks a little tir=
ed, we should do something to cheer him up and let him know that we=E2=80=
=99re thinking of him,=E2=80=9D and one director suggested leaving a Post-I=
t note on his monitor saying =E2=80=9Cjust wanted to say that we appreciate=
 you,=E2=80=9D and another director was like =E2=80=9Chey that's a great id=
ea but let's also put $50 million under the note=E2=80=9D and everyone else=
 was like =E2=80=9Coh well of course yes $50 million.=E2=80=9D And he walke=
d in to see the filing and was like =E2=80=9Coh that was nice of them=E2=80=
=9D and smiled for a minute and got back to work and never thought of the $=
50 million again, it's just $50 million, who cares.It is weird though. It i=
s hard for me to imagine how an extra $50 million could add anything to Dim=
on=E2=80=99s motivation. (=E2=80=9CThe purpose of this award is to motivate=
 your future performance for future services,=E2=80=9D says the award agree=
ment.) Presumably he already cares a lot about his reputation, and about=C2=
=A0the bank that he helped to build and that he=E2=80=99s run for the last =
16 years? And to the extent he=E2=80=99s motivated by money, presumably his=
 9.4 million shares of JPMorgan stock already provide a lot of incentive to=
 make the stock go up.On the other hand it does seem like this award would =
be=C2=A0bad=C2=A0for the motivation of Dimon=E2=80=99s senior lieutenants a=
nd potential successors? It has been a long-running joke in finance that Di=
mon=E2=80=99s successors keep leaving before he does. The latest round of =
=E2=80=9Chere are some new Jamie Dimon=C2=A0successors=E2=80=9D was just tw=
o months ago; it can=E2=80=99t be all that reassuring for them that the boa=
rd almost immediately decided to give Dimon $50 million more to stick aroun=
d until they leave too.=C2=A0
