      Not this again
   =20
 =20
This is gonna be great:What are the odds that two companies with almost ide=
ntical names would go public on the same exact day?However rare, this is ha=
ppening.=C2=A0Zevia PBC, which makes zero-sugar beverages, and=C2=A0Zenvia =
Inc., which will hold all share capital in data source aggregator Direct On=
e, are both expected to price initial public offerings on Wednesday.It=E2=
=80=99s an improbable coincidence hitting the calendar for new issues and c=
ould potentially lead to mistaken-identity trades. Even their tickers are s=
imilar: Zevia will use the symbol ZVIA and Zenvia will use the symbol ZENV.=
Signal vs.  Signal, COKE vs.  Coca-Cola, Zoom vs.  Zoom, Snapchat vs.  SNAP=
, Nest vs.  Nestor, now Zevia vs. Zenvia. Now we just need=C2=A0Elon Musk t=
o tweet =E2=80=9CI love drinking zero-sugar beverages while looking at aggr=
egated data and I=E2=80=99m going to buy Znevia for $420.69 per share=E2=80=
=9D and see what happens.
