</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What happened <a href=3D"https://link.=
mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24514165.265021/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZX=
JnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDctMjAvanBtb3JnYW4tYm9hcmQtYXdhcmRzLWNlb=
y1kaW1vbi1zdG9jay1vcHRpb25zLXRvLXN0YXktYXQtYmFuaw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB=
844ff28f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
 here</a>?</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Jamie Dimon=E2=80=99=
s five-year retirement joke just got serious.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0=
;">The billionaire chief executive officer of JPMorgan Chase &amp; Co. was =
granted a special gift to persuade him to lead the biggest U.S. lender for =
another =E2=80=9Csignificant number of years.=E2=80=9D He was awarded 1.5 m=
illion stock appreciation rights, which are like options and will let him c=
apture a profit if the stock price rises in the coming years. =E2=80=A6</p>=
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThis special award reflects the board=
=E2=80=99s desire for Mr. Dimon to continue to lead the firm for a further =
significant number of years,=E2=80=9D JPMorgan=E2=80=99s board said in a re=
gulatory filing Tuesday.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Dimon=E2=80=99s op=
