o thing is a security, then it basically needs to be=C2=A0(1)=C2=A0register=
ed with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, (2) only sold to =E2=
=80=9Caccredited investors=E2=80=9D (with $1 million of net worth or $200,0=
00 of annual income)=C2=A0or (3) not offered in the U.S. If it=E2=80=99s no=
t a security, then there=E2=80=99s a lot more flexibility to sell it and tr=
ade it widely.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Some crypto things are secur=
ities, some are not, and a lot are sort of unclear. Bitcoin is not a securi=
ty. Ethereum is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24=
