rop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-dec=
oration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0=
00000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">probably not a =
security</a>. A few years ago there was a big vogue for initial coin offeri=
ngs=C2=A0to fund all sorts of platforms and businesses, which were sold wid=
ely because people thought they might not be securities; the SEC <a href=3D=
"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24514165.265021/aHR0cHM6Ly93=
d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTktMTAtMTQvdGhlLXNlYy1yZWF=
sbHktZG9lc24tdC1saWtlLWljb3M/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7d4349a3" itemprop=3D=
"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoratio=
n: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000;=
 border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> took a very hard lin=
e</a> that they were basically all securities, and the ICO boom died down.<=
/p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A very popular crypto thing these days is w=
hat I=E2=80=99ll loosely call =E2=80=9Clending programs.=E2=80=9D You own s=
ome cryptocurrency coins, you pop them into some sort of pool, the pool use=
s your coins to make money (by market making, or by proprietary trading, or=
 by lending them out to people who want to borrow crypto), and the pool sha=
res the money it makes with you. Lots of =E2=80=9Cyield farming=E2=80=9D an=
d =E2=80=9Cautomated market making=E2=80=9D programs have this basic struct=
ure, and it is very popular in the decentralized-finance world.</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It is also obviously a security? In U.S. law, the =E2=
=80=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24514165.265=
