rather than a human manager =E2=80=94=C2=A0if it's an automated market make=
r where you can review the source code for yourself=C2=A0and where no one h=
as discretion to change it =E2=80=94=C2=A0then you have an interesting argu=
ment. (Maybe it=E2=80=99s not a security because the profits are not =E2=80=
=9Cderived from the efforts of others,=E2=80=9D exactly, or maybe it=C2=A0<=
em>is=C2=A0</em>a security but there=E2=80=99s no one for the SEC to sue.) =
But if some corporate entity manages the lending or trading or market-makin=
g pool then there is going to be trouble.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">S=
o we <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24514165.2650=
